        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 11:04PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1104 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of Pampa, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pampa, Lefors, Kingsmill, and Codman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
